               <head>Sharḥ-i Qirān al-saʿdayn by Nūr al-Ḥaqq Dihlavī</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2010105563">
                  <summary>A commentary on the poem <title key="work_888">Qirān al-saʿdayn</title>,
                     by <persName role="ant" key="VIAF_76503034">Amīr Khusrau Dihlavī</persName>
                     (1251-1325), composed by Nūr al-Ḥaqq ibn ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq al-Mashriqī al-Dihlavī
                     al-Bukhārī (d.1662-3) </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1239-item1">
                     <author key="VIAF_4163208250607231592">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Nūr al-Ḥaqq Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">نور الحق دهلوی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="">Sharḥ-i Qirān al-saʿdayn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">شرح قران السّعدین</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">خطبۀ کبریا و جلال بر پادشاهی که او را آغاز و انجام
                        نیست.</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">دور نیست که گویند شمشیر بعضی اوقات از گردن
                        اوست.</explicit>
                     <colophon>(f. 77v) Completed on 27 Ramazan year 23 [possibly of Akbar Shah II,
                        r. 1806-1837 (2 April 1829)]. </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>Covers only the first part of the work. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
